We hear frequently from our best educated public speakers and from many a teacher’s desk mistakes which a rigid drilling in the use of the English pronunciation would have prevented. Thus derivation, meaning, and pronunciation favor decidedly the system that has been employed in England since the reign of Elizabeth.
